Four Nyandarua MPs have praised President Uhuru Kenyatta for rejecting calls to amend the Cosntitution. Michael Muchira (Ol Joro Orok), Zachary Kwenya (Kinangop), David Kiaraho (Ol Kalou) and Amos Kimunya (Kipipiri) on Saturday said Kenyans cannot afford a referendum. On Friday, Uhuru told manufacturers at State House that he had no time to campaign for a vote to change the law. "I want to thank our party leader for giving the right direction. We will not change the Constitution," Muchira said. The MPs spoke at Rurinja Stadium in Kinangop. Click here for the latest political news 